A minimalistic illustration of two tall, translucent filing cabinets standing side by side, connected by flowing streams of glowing blue particles that arc gracefully between their open drawers. The particles move in both directions, suggesting bidirectional synchronization. The cabinets are rendered in soft gray tones against a clean white background with subtle shadows. Inside each cabinet, abstract document shapes in muted colors are visible, some highlighted with a gentle pulse of light where the particle streams touch them. The overall composition is balanced and serene, with generous negative space and a sense of quiet efficiency and harmony between the two structures.
